newsitem.title: USA: CBOT overnight Project A ag volume 3,794 contracts.
newsitem.headline: CBOT overnight Project A ag volume 3,794 contracts.

text.p: Chicago Board of Trade's Project A overnight agricultural contracts trading volume totalled 3,794 contracts, according to the CBOT.
There were 66 wheat, 1,388 corn, 1,898 soybean, 95 soymeal, 335 soyoil and 12 oats futures contracts traded along with 7 wheat put, 2 corn call and 11 soybean call options.

The overnight trend for corn was down 2 to 2-3/4 cents per bushel, soybeans down 5-3/4 to 7 cents, wheat down 2 to 3-1/2 cents, soymeal down $1.90 to $2.70 per ton, soyoil down 0.13 cent per lb and oats down 1/2 cent per bushel.
